payload.message:
**Post Wiring**
- `packages/domains/post/package.json:6-18` now publishes `Post`/`PostPort` directly so every consumer can import the exact module they need without relying on a missing index file.
- `packages/domains/post/src/Post.ts:5-31` and `packages/domains/post/src/PostPort.ts:2-32` were moved under `src/` and updated to reference each other via the new subpaths.

**Adapters & Services**
- `packages/adapters/post/PostAdapterConsole.ts:3-44` and `packages/adapters/post/PostAdapterPostgre.ts:2-19` point at `@domains/post/Post*`; the Postgre adapter now pulls its pool from the new `@infra/postgre` workspace package (`packages/adapters/post/package.json:2-31`, `packages/infras/postgre/package.json:1-19`, `packages/infras/postgre/src/pool.ts:1-10`, `packages/infras/postgre/tsconfig.json:1-16`).
- `packages/services/post/PostService.ts:2-20` builds posts through the domain factory, and `packages/services/post/package.json:2-32` exposes both service and layer entrypoints with correct adapter/domain/effect dependencies.
- `packages/infras/supabase/tsconfig.json:15-16` no longer points at the removed `index.ts`, matching the new domain layout.

**Template**
- `template/web/astro/package.json:12-31` declares `@services/post` and `effect`, ensuring the Astro page resolves the DI stack end-to-end.

No tests were run—recommend `pnpm install` (to pick up the new workspace packages) followed by the relevant dev or test command once dependencies are in place. One follow-up to note: `packages/infras/supabase/src/post.ts` still expects the old domain shape (e.g. `CreatePost`, decoders). Adjust or remove that module when you tackle the Supabase integration.
